A tester executes a large number of test cases and reports that no defects were found.
Questions:

Does this mean the system has no defects? Why or why not?
Which fundamental testing principle applies here?
What risks remain despite finding no defects?

Answers:
1. No the absence of detected defects does not mean there aren't any
2. See above
3. Remaining risks would include untested paths, unknown usage patterns
